      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GO PIKACHU (1) stalked the lead but wound up strongly to score (25.93) at this track in Grade 5 over 450m. Looks to have an edge on most of these. ASCEND IGLOO (4) is a capable type and proved too classy last time to win by 1.3 lengths at Shepparton in a handy 25.96 beating Aussie Flame. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in his latest win. Has hit winning form and can go on with it. PATTY'S DREAM (7) was below best latest but did hit the frame in quick time two back when third (29.29) at Bendigo in a Grade 5. Key player on best and worth another try. VINTAGE KING (3) missed the placings here most recently but can sneak into the finish with the right run.",
